title: Chair Seat, 1800–10
medium:
Medium: linen, silk
Technique: counted stitch embroidery
description: Octagonal medallion of upholstery fabric illustrating a fable by La Fontaine known as "The Deer and the Vine" or "The Deer and his Antlers." The pattern is in white and shades of yellow on a light blue ground.
